09/01/2011
COPENHAGEN, Denmark -- Police arrested a Bosnian-born Swedish citizen suspected of war crimes committed in former Yugoslavia on Thursday (January 6th) at Copenhagen's international airport. The 42-year man was detained based on an arrest warrant issued by Slovenia in 2007. Slovenian authorities want him in connection with a shooting incident at a Slovenian border crossing in 1991. The identity of the suspect was not revealed. (Radio Free Europe, AFP - 07/01/11)
